[{"id":"A-DASH-1","severity":"critical","file":"dashboard/server.py","line":"154","issue":"Multiple state-changing dashboard endpoints are reachable without authentication or authorization, allowing remote users to trigger workflows and modify live ops/trading state.","evidence":"`app = FastAPI(...)` is created with no auth dependency or middleware, and POST handlers such as `/api/trigger` (lines 154-190), `/api/outreach/update-status` (330-361), `/api/outreach/followup-sweep` (364-384), `/api/landing/deploy` (410-452), `/api/runway/revive` (463-467), `/api/opportunity/grade` (470-483), `/api/revenue/log` (486-498), and `/api/spawn-schedules` (650-676) execute privileged actions directly from request data.","fix":"Require authenticated operator access with per-route authorization on all non-public endpoints and enforce CSRF protection for browser-initiated POSTs.","confidence":"high"},{"id":"A-DASH-2","severity":"high","file":"dashboard/server.py","line":"85","issue":"Sensitive live trading and internal ops data is exposed to unauthenticated clients through read endpoints and WebSockets.","evidence":"`/state` returns the full dashboard state file (lines 85-87), `/ws` accepts any WebSocket client and immediately sends `_read_state()` (90-99), and endpoints such as `/api/tony/book` (1033-1058), `/api/pnl` (501-522), `/api/activity` (193-229), `/api/vault/feed` (696-725), and `/api/tony/live` in `dashboard/tony_routes.py` (88-325) expose live positions, verdicts, revenue, task activity, and vault session summaries with no access control.","fix":"Restrict sensitive read endpoints and WebSockets to authenticated/authorized users and redact fields that are not required by the caller.","confidence":"high"},{"id":"A-DASH-3","severity":"high","file":"dashboard/server.py","line":"418","issue":"`/api/landing/deploy` trusts the client-supplied `slug` when constructing a filesystem path, enabling path traversal and arbitrary `index.html` modification outside the sites directory.","evidence":"The handler takes `slug` from `request.json()` (lines 418-421), builds `index = SITES_DIR / slug / \"index.html\"` (line 430), then reads and rewrites that file with attacker-influenced content via `index.write_text(...)` (line 436) without normalizing `slug` or verifying that the resolved path stays under `SITES_DIR`. A `slug` containing `../` or `..\\\\` can escape the intended root.","fix":"Validate `slug` against a strict allowlist such as `^[a-z0-9-]+$` and reject any resolved path that is not contained within `SITES_DIR`.","confidence":"med"},{"id":"A-DASH-4","severity":"medium","file":"dashboard/server.py","line":"393","issue":"The 404 response for `/sites/{slug}` reflects unescaped user input into HTML, enabling reflected XSS.","evidence":"When no built page exists, the handler returns `HTMLResponse(f\"<h1>No built page for {slug!r} yet.</h1>\")` (line 393). `slug` comes from the URL path and is inserted directly into HTML without escaping, so HTML/JS payloads are reflected to the browser.","fix":"HTML-escape `slug` before rendering or return a static error message that does not include raw user input.","confidence":"high"},{"id":"A-DASH-5","severity":"medium","file":"dashboard/server.py","line":"341","issue":"Several endpoints perform unlocked read-modify-write updates on shared files, creating TOCTOU/lost-update races that can corrupt operator state.","evidence":"`/api/outreach/update-status` reads `vault/outreach/crm.md`, edits an in-memory line list, and rewrites the whole file (341-359) while autonomous workers can update the same CRM; `/api/spawn-schedules` rewrites `spawn-schedules.yaml` similarly (655-674); `/api/landing/deploy` rewrites site HTML and appends to `upsell-catalog.md` without any lock (433-449). Concurrent requests or background jobs can overwrite each other's changes.","fix":"Use file locking plus atomic replace/version checks, or move these mutable records into a transactional datastore.","confidence":"high"},{"id":"A-DASH-6","severity":"medium","file":"dashboard/tony_routes.py","line":"45","issue":"Multiple endpoints return raw exception text to unauthenticated clients, leaking internal error details from broker, filesystem, and ledger code.","evidence":"Handlers return `{\"error\": str(exc)}` or embed `str(exc)` directly in responses, including `/api/tony/record` (39-46), `/api/tony/agreement` (49-62), `/api/spx` (65-72), `/api/marks` (75-85), `/api/tony/book` in `dashboard/server.py` (1056-1058), and `/api/tony/equity-curve` (1067-1070). Any remote caller can harvest internal failure text.","fix":"Log detailed exceptions server-side and return only generic client-facing errors or opaque error IDs.","confidence":"med"}]
